            {
              "id": "CVE-2022-29155",
              "name": "Package vulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2022-29155"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "In OpenLDAP 2.x before 2.5.12 and 2.6.x before 2.6.2, a SQL injection vulnerability exists in the experimental back-sql backend to slapd, via a SQL statement within an LDAP query. This can occur during an LDAP search operation when the search filter is processed, due to a lack of proper escaping."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2022-29155",
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "9.0",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
                  "security",
                  "critical",
                  "has-exploit"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2021-3520",
              "name": "Package vulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2021-3520"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "There\u0026#39;s a flaw in lz4. An attacker who submits a crafted file to an application linked with lz4 may be able to trigger an integer overflow, leading to calling of memmove() on a negative size argument, causing an out-of-bounds write and/or a crash. The greatest impact of this flaw is to availability, with some potential impact to confidentiality and integrity as well."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2021-3520",
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
                "security-severity": "9.0",
                "tags": [
                  "vulnerability",
                  "security",
                  "critical",
                  "has-exploit"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2019-3858",
              "name": "Package vulnerability",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2019-3858"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "An out of bounds read flaw was discovered in libssh2 before 1.8.1 when a specially crafted SFTP packet is received from the server. A remote attacker who compromises a SSH server may be able to cause a Denial of Service or read data in the client memory."
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "error"
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-3858",
              "properties": {
                "precision": "very-high",
