          "message": {
            "text": "Name: CVE-2022-1664\nSeverity: Critical\nComponent: dpkg-dev\nType: Package vulnerability\nVersion: 1.18.25\nFixed version: 1.18.26\nSource: [CVE-2022-1664](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2022-1664)\nDescription: Dpkg::Source::Archive in dpkg, the Debian package management system, before version 1.21.8, 1.20.10, 1.19.8, 1.18.26 is prone to a directory traversal vulnerability. When extracting untrusted source packages in v2 and v3 source package formats that include a debian.tar, the in-place extraction can lead to directory traversal situations on specially crafted orig.tar and debian.tar tarballs.",
            "markdown": "\n### 🌟 TL;DR\n- Package vulnerability was detected in component `dpkg-dev` version `1.18.25`\n- Vulnerable to [**`CVE-2022-1664`**](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2022-1664)\n- Fixed version: `1.18.26`\n### 🔍 Overview\nDpkg::Source::Archive in dpkg, the Debian package management system, before version 1.21.8, 1.20.10, 1.19.8, 1.18.26 is prone to a directory traversal vulnerability. When extracting untrusted source packages in v2 and v3 source package formats that include a debian.tar, the in-place extraction can lead to directory traversal situations on specially crafted orig.tar and debian.tar tarballs.\n\n\n### 🔗 References\n- [Data Source](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2022-1664)\n- [View finding in Wiz](https://app.wiz.io/findings/vulnerability-findings#~(entity~(~%271c87583e-0adc-50e3-9b16-c929bfc118ee*2cSECURITY_TOOL_FINDING)))\n- [View vulnerability in catalog](https://app.wiz.io/policies/vulnerability-catalog#~(filters~(search~(contains~%27CVE-2022-1664))~cve~%27CVE-2022-1664))\n"
          },
