            "text": "Name: CVE-2019-20367\nSeverity: Critical\nComponent: libbsd0\nType: Package vulnerability\nVersion: 0.8.3-1\nFixed version: 0.8.3-1+deb9u1\nSource: [CVE-2019-20367](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-20367)\nDescription: nlist.c in libbsd before 0.10.0 has an out-of-bounds read during a comparison for a symbol name from the string table (strtab).",
            "markdown": "\n### 🌟 TL;DR\n- Package vulnerability was detected in component `libbsd0` version `0.8.3-1`\n- Vulnerable to [**`CVE-2019-20367`**](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-20367)\n- Fixed version: `0.8.3-1+deb9u1`\n### 🔍 Overview\nnlist.c in libbsd before 0.10.0 has an out-of-bounds read during a comparison for a symbol name from the string table (strtab).\n\n\n### 🔗 References\n- [Data Source](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-20367)\n- [View finding in Wiz](https://app.wiz.io/findings/vulnerability-findings#~(entity~(~%27bb21c6f7-9e2d-5e41-859b-77d52289e1aa*2cSECURITY_TOOL_FINDING)))\n- [View vulnerability in catalog](https://app.wiz.io/policies/vulnerability-catalog#~(filters~(search~(contains~%27CVE-2019-20367))~cve~%27CVE-2019-20367))\n"
