          "ruleId": "CVE-2019-12450",
          "ruleIndex": 6,
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Name: CVE-2019-12450\nSeverity: Critical\nComponent: libglib2.0-0\nType: Package vulnerability\nVersion: 2.50.3-2\nFixed version: 2.50.3-2+deb9u1\nSource: [CVE-2019-12450](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-12450)\nDescription: file_copy_fallback in gio/gfile.c in GNOME GLib 2.15.0 through 2.61.1 does not properly restrict file permissions while a copy operation is in progress. Instead, default permissions are used.",
            "markdown": "\n### 🌟 TL;DR\n- Package vulnerability was detected in component `libglib2.0-0` version `2.50.3-2`\n- Vulnerable to [**`CVE-2019-12450`**](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-12450)\n- Fixed version: `2.50.3-2+deb9u1`\n### 🔍 Overview\nfile_copy_fallback in gio/gfile.c in GNOME GLib 2.15.0 through 2.61.1 does not properly restrict file permissions while a copy operation is in progress. Instead, default permissions are used.\n\n\n### 🔗 References\n- [Data Source](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-12450)\n- [View finding in Wiz](https://app.wiz.io/findings/vulnerability-findings#~(entity~(~%2749c8ac99-ff88-524e-bf1e-2cbd95d78f71*2cSECURITY_TOOL_FINDING)))\n- [View vulnerability in catalog](https://app.wiz.io/policies/vulnerability-catalog#~(filters~(search~(contains~%27CVE-2019-12450))~cve~%27CVE-2019-12450))\n"
          },
