            "markdown": "\n### 🌟 TL;DR\n- Package vulnerability was detected in component `libidn11` version `1.33-1`\n- Vulnerable to [**`CVE-2017-14062`**](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2017-14062)\n- Fixed version: `1.33-1+deb9u1`\n### 🔍 Overview\nInteger overflow in the decode_digit function in puny_decode.c in Libidn2 before 2.0.4 allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service or possibly have unspecified other impact.\n\n\n### 🔗 References\n- [Data Source](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2017-14062)\n- [View finding in Wiz](https://app.wiz.io/findings/vulnerability-findings#~(entity~(~%2749e08ac6-6616-533d-a645-d97996f1dc56*2cSECURITY_TOOL_FINDING)))\n- [View vulnerability in catalog](https://app.wiz.io/policies/vulnerability-catalog#~(filters~(search~(contains~%27CVE-2017-14062))~cve~%27CVE-2017-14062))\n"
