        {
          "ruleId": "CVE-2022-29155",
          "ruleIndex": 8,
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Name: CVE-2022-29155\nSeverity: Critical\nComponent: libldap-common\nType: Package vulnerability\nVersion: 2.4.44+dfsg-5+deb9u2\nFixed version: 2.4.44+dfsg-5+deb9u9\nSource: [CVE-2022-29155](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2022-29155)\nDescription: In OpenLDAP 2.x before 2.5.12 and 2.6.x before 2.6.2, a SQL injection vulnerability exists in the experimental back-sql backend to slapd, via a SQL statement within an LDAP query. This can occur during an LDAP search operation when the search filter is processed, due to a lack of proper escaping.",
            "markdown": "\n### 🌟 TL;DR\n- Package vulnerability was detected in component `libldap-common` version `2.4.44+dfsg-5+deb9u2`\n- Vulnerable to [**`CVE-2022-29155`**](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2022-29155)\n- Fixed version: `2.4.44+dfsg-5+deb9u9`\n### 🔍 Overview\nIn OpenLDAP 2.x before 2.5.12 and 2.6.x before 2.6.2, a SQL injection vulnerability exists in the experimental back-sql backend to slapd, via a SQL statement within an LDAP query. This can occur during an LDAP search operation when the search filter is processed, due to a lack of proper escaping.\n\n\n### 🔗 References\n- [Data Source](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2022-29155)\n- [View finding in Wiz](https://app.wiz.io/findings/vulnerability-findings#~(entity~(~%27cb993193-894b-5728-ae89-69d468966b04*2cSECURITY_TOOL_FINDING)))\n- [View vulnerability in catalog](https://app.wiz.io/policies/vulnerability-catalog#~(filters~(search~(contains~%27CVE-2022-29155))~cve~%27CVE-2022-29155))\n"
          },
