          "ruleId": "CVE-2021-3520",
          "ruleIndex": 9,
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Name: CVE-2021-3520\nSeverity: Critical\nComponent: liblz4-1\nType: Package vulnerability\nVersion: 0.0~r131-2+b1\nFixed version: 0.0~r131-2+deb9u1\nSource: [CVE-2021-3520](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2021-3520)\nDescription: There's a flaw in lz4. An attacker who submits a crafted file to an application linked with lz4 may be able to trigger an integer overflow, leading to calling of memmove() on a negative size argument, causing an out-of-bounds write and/or a crash. The greatest impact of this flaw is to availability, with some potential impact to confidentiality and integrity as well.",
            "markdown": "\n### 🌟 TL;DR\n- Package vulnerability was detected in component `liblz4-1` version `0.0~r131-2+b1`\n- Vulnerable to [**`CVE-2021-3520`**](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2021-3520)\n- Fixed version: `0.0~r131-2+deb9u1`\n### 🔍 Overview\nThere's a flaw in lz4. An attacker who submits a crafted file to an application linked with lz4 may be able to trigger an integer overflow, leading to calling of memmove() on a negative size argument, causing an out-of-bounds write and/or a crash. The greatest impact of this flaw is to availability, with some potential impact to confidentiality and integrity as well.\n\n\n### 🔗 References\n- [Data Source](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2021-3520)\n- [View finding in Wiz](https://app.wiz.io/findings/vulnerability-findings#~(entity~(~%27592f9006-8dab-54c8-a6c3-f4cd02ec83ad*2cSECURITY_TOOL_FINDING)))\n- [View vulnerability in catalog](https://app.wiz.io/policies/vulnerability-catalog#~(filters~(search~(contains~%27CVE-2021-3520))~cve~%27CVE-2021-3520))\n"
          },
          "locations": [
