          "ruleId": "CVE-2019-3860",
          "ruleIndex": 12,
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Name: CVE-2019-3860\nSeverity: Critical\nComponent: libssh2-1\nType: Package vulnerability\nVersion: 1.7.0-1\nFixed version: 1.7.0-1+deb9u1\nSource: [CVE-2019-3860](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-3860)\nDescription: An out of bounds read flaw was discovered in libssh2 before 1.8.1 in the way SFTP packets with empty payloads are parsed. A remote attacker who compromises a SSH server may be able to cause a Denial of Service or read data in the client memory.",
            "markdown": "\n### 🌟 TL;DR\n- Package vulnerability was detected in component `libssh2-1` version `1.7.0-1`\n- Vulnerable to [**`CVE-2019-3860`**](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-3860)\n- Fixed version: `1.7.0-1+deb9u1`\n### 🔍 Overview\nAn out of bounds read flaw was discovered in libssh2 before 1.8.1 in the way SFTP packets with empty payloads are parsed. A remote attacker who compromises a SSH server may be able to cause a Denial of Service or read data in the client memory.\n\n\n### 🔗 References\n- [Data Source](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-3860)\n- [View finding in Wiz](https://app.wiz.io/findings/vulnerability-findings#~(entity~(~%278f08e382-e7d5-5fe5-bf86-ef454b539954*2cSECURITY_TOOL_FINDING)))\n- [View vulnerability in catalog](https://app.wiz.io/policies/vulnerability-catalog#~(filters~(search~(contains~%27CVE-2019-3860))~cve~%27CVE-2019-3860))\n"
