        {
          "ruleId": "CVE-2019-3862",
          "ruleIndex": 14,
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Name: CVE-2019-3862\nSeverity: Critical\nComponent: libssh2-1\nType: Package vulnerability\nVersion: 1.7.0-1\nFixed version: 1.7.0-1+deb9u1\nSource: [CVE-2019-3862](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-3862)\nDescription: An out of bounds read flaw was discovered in libssh2 before 1.8.1 in the way SSH_MSG_CHANNEL_REQUEST packets with an exit status message and no payload are parsed. A remote attacker who compromises a SSH server may be able to cause a Denial of Service or read data in the client memory.",
            "markdown": "\n### 🌟 TL;DR\n- Package vulnerability was detected in component `libssh2-1` version `1.7.0-1`\n- Vulnerable to [**`CVE-2019-3862`**](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-3862)\n- Fixed version: `1.7.0-1+deb9u1`\n### 🔍 Overview\nAn out of bounds read flaw was discovered in libssh2 before 1.8.1 in the way SSH_MSG_CHANNEL_REQUEST packets with an exit status message and no payload are parsed. A remote attacker who compromises a SSH server may be able to cause a Denial of Service or read data in the client memory.\n\n\n### 🔗 References\n- [Data Source](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2019-3862)\n- [View finding in Wiz](https://app.wiz.io/findings/vulnerability-findings#~(entity~(~%276972f25b-845f-5ad3-b289-0a87a73a3544*2cSECURITY_TOOL_FINDING)))\n- [View vulnerability in catalog](https://app.wiz.io/policies/vulnerability-catalog#~(filters~(search~(contains~%27CVE-2019-3862))~cve~%27CVE-2019-3862))\n"
